      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/uq-003-pressure-head-gci"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-004-hemolysis-sensitivity-operating-point",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis sensitivity to operating point variation \u2014 qualitative variability assessment only",
      "description": "CFD hemolysis predictions evaluated across a design-of-experiments sweep of five flow-speed combinations to identify worst-case conditions. Biological variability in red blood cell fragility across donor samples and inter-run variability in the hemolysis assay were noted by the analyst as sources of aleatory uncertainty. The assessment team concluded that inherent variability was assessed qualitatively based on published literature ranges and engineering judgment; no structured UQ node was constructed or linked for this result, as the variability was deemed bounded by the conservative RH < 1 acceptance criterion."
    }
